02:27.522 --> 02:31.608
Shush, please,
please, everybody quiet.

02:34.740 --> 02:37.129
Hey, Mom, how you doing?

02:37.130 --> 02:39.099
Ever since Dad passed away,

02:39.100 --> 02:41.550
you've raised us both like
a mother and a father.

02:42.510 --> 02:45.299
In honor of your birthday,
I made a small home video

02:45.300 --> 02:48.259
of the recording you made
of Elenie and I growing up.

02:48.260 --> 02:52.929
And Mom, you don't look a
day older than 55 years old.

02:52.930 --> 02:53.844
Love you, Mom.

05:36.960 --> 05:37.991
Mom, what are you trying to say,

05:37.992 --> 05:40.718
a woman can't be married
and have a career too?

05:40.719 --> 05:41.552
Is that what you're saying?

05:41.553 --> 05:44.519
What is the point of owning a house

05:44.520 --> 05:46.909
if you don't have anyone to live with?

05:46.910 --> 05:50.379
So, Mom, I'm gonna
marry a burger-loving,

05:50.380 --> 05:53.549
pale American man and
share my home with him.

05:53.550 --> 05:55.989
Hey, here we go again.

05:55.990 --> 05:57.889
Well, find me a
burger-loving Ethiopian man.

05:57.890 --> 05:59.639
Your father was a great man.

05:59.640 --> 06:01.729
They don't make men like that anymore.

06:30.655 --> 06:32.949
You are not going to
sleep with his accent.

06:32.950 --> 06:34.372
Oh, Mom.

07:06.650 --> 07:07.975
Abell, you're leaving?

07:07.976 --> 07:09.317
Honey, honey!

07:14.859 --> 07:15.692
Feel like I'm drowning here.

07:15.693 --> 07:17.209
Nah, you're not drowning,

07:17.210 --> 07:18.799
just got a little water-logged.

07:18.800 --> 07:20.269
Hey, talking about my weight?

07:20.270 --> 07:23.178
No, I know I'm fat, but you
can't do that.

07:27.767 --> 07:29.033
All right, sweetheart.

07:54.349 --> 07:56.599
Lena, if you were married,

07:56.600 --> 07:58.539
there would be more pleasurable way

07:58.540 --> 08:00.062
to work out a sweat.

08:00.063 --> 08:01.636
Mom, that is so disgusting, you know?

08:01.637 --> 08:02.979
And could you please knock the door

08:02.980 --> 08:04.763
when you come to my room next time?

08:07.333 --> 08:09.785
There are no boundaries in this household.

08:09.786 --> 08:11.951
Elenie,

08:11.952 --> 08:12.850
Elenie!

08:12.851 --> 08:15.229
No, not Yohance.
Kiss me!

08:15.230 --> 08:16.683
Mom, I grew up with him!

08:18.620 --> 08:21.039
He's like my brother, and
he saw me pee in my pants

08:21.040 --> 08:22.463
when I was five, no.

08:23.586 --> 08:26.663
You know, he works with his hand.

08:27.900 --> 08:28.830
He's a surgeon.

08:28.831 --> 08:32.513
Oh, no, yuck, that is not right, no!

08:40.679 --> 08:43.299
You should date him
'cause you're single.

08:43.299 --> 08:45.533
I'm gonna arrange it, it's settled.

09:01.846 --> 09:03.103
Elenie Tariku.

09:03.104 --> 09:05.009
Hi, Mrs. Tariku.

09:05.010 --> 09:08.354
This is Officer Freedman with the NYPD.

10:34.829 --> 10:35.746
You know,

10:36.753 --> 10:37.670
it's funny.

10:39.117 --> 10:41.449
When Abell and I were in college,

10:41.450 --> 10:43.400
he used to irritate the hell out of me,

10:45.120 --> 10:47.589
'cause it seemed like
he had this fascination

10:47.590 --> 10:50.879
with hammering nails in
the most random places

10:50.880 --> 10:52.649
to hang his pants.

10:52.650 --> 10:55.059
So of course, I'd wake up and hit my head

10:55.060 --> 10:56.623
on those things every morning.

10:59.480 --> 11:02.619
When he moved out, he took
all his nails with him.

11:02.620 --> 11:04.259
This morning, I woke up having the urge

11:04.260 --> 11:06.633
to start filling all the
holes back with nails.

11:08.980 --> 11:12.659
Then I realized I wouldn't
have anyone to blame

11:12.660 --> 11:13.893
for my clumsiness.

11:15.810 --> 11:16.643
Your brother,

11:18.230 --> 11:20.623
he didn't mind taking the blame
for other people's faults.

11:25.972 --> 11:28.805
If you ever need someone, call me.

11:31.654 --> 11:32.853
Thank you, Yohance.

14:04.927 --> 14:07.889
Charley, you hit Madison pretty hard.

14:07.890 --> 14:10.619
She had to go and see a
doctor, she was hurt by you.

14:10.620 --> 14:11.739
I should apologize for him,

14:11.740 --> 14:14.519
but I've never been
very good at apologies.

14:14.520 --> 14:16.399
I'm the dad, I'm Logan.

14:16.400 --> 14:17.439
Think your mom let me in.

14:17.440 --> 14:19.109
Oh, yeah, sorry about that,

14:19.110 --> 14:20.579
my mother is helping me out today.

14:20.580 --> 14:22.162
Come on in, I'm Elenie Tariku.

14:22.163 --> 14:23.329
Hey, Logan Thompson.

14:23.330 --> 14:24.879
Nice to meet you.

14:24.880 --> 14:27.179
Charley, I need to speak
to your father privately.

14:27.180 --> 14:28.839
Do you mind waiting in the hallway?

14:28.840 --> 14:30.689
He's gonna tell me what you say anyways.

14:30.690 --> 14:32.940
Wipe that tone of
voice off your face, bud.

14:34.160 --> 14:35.010
Come on, come on.

14:42.413 --> 14:43.620
I don't know what's been going on with him

14:43.621 --> 14:44.880
these last few months.

14:44.881 --> 14:45.812
Oh, he'll be fine.

14:45.813 --> 14:48.869
You know, when kids move to a
new school, a new environment,

14:48.870 --> 14:50.369
they tend to act out.

14:50.370 --> 14:51.589
My wife and I are from here.

14:51.590 --> 14:54.349
We actually went to the same
school, good old Larsen Hill,

14:54.350 --> 14:56.089
except I was the one beatin' up on kids.

14:56.090 --> 14:58.169
So where did you move from?

14:58.170 --> 14:59.080
Troy, Michigan.

14:59.081 --> 15:01.730
My wife got this great job
opportunity at,

15:03.080 --> 15:06.123
and I got laid off.

15:12.040 --> 15:14.389
Mr. Thompson, it is your
right to refuse counseling,

15:14.390 --> 15:16.729
but considering this is
Charley's second outburst,

15:16.730 --> 15:18.586
if he continues this way,
the school will expel him.

15:18.587 --> 15:20.233
You can call me Logan.

15:21.980 --> 15:23.380
Your eyes are so expressive.

15:25.070 --> 15:27.189
It's because they're
big, isn't it?

15:27.190 --> 15:28.390
No, they're beautiful.

15:31.460 --> 15:33.939
Isn't it funny the things
you were teased for as a child,

15:33.940 --> 15:37.193
you always get complimented
on as an adult, right?

15:38.190 --> 15:39.100
Where are you from?

15:39.101 --> 15:40.689
I mean, if you don't mind me asking.

15:40.690 --> 15:43.089
I'm from Ethiopia, do
you know where that is?

15:43.090 --> 15:44.490
Of course you do, I'm sorry.

15:46.028 --> 15:48.359
If I'm not mistaken, it's
the birthplace of coffee?

15:48.360 --> 15:49.769
Wow, I'm impressed.

15:49.770 --> 15:51.789
You know, most people would
jump straight to the famine

15:51.790 --> 15:53.169
we had back in the '80s.

15:53.170 --> 15:54.779
I got some good jokes.

15:54.780 --> 15:57.310
No, I'm totally...

15:58.340 --> 15:59.890
I'm kidding, that's ridiculous.

16:03.590 --> 16:08.069
Anyways, I recommend Charley
and I meet twice a week.

16:08.070 --> 16:10.299
Doctor knows best.

16:10.300 --> 16:12.800
I'm not a doctor,
I'm just a counselor.

16:20.340 --> 16:23.006
Six seconds, you ready for this?

16:23.007 --> 16:25.329
He dribbles, he dribbles,

16:25.330 --> 16:27.889
six, five, dribbling really quietly

16:27.890 --> 16:29.719
because the neighbors are asleep.

16:29.720 --> 16:32.173
All right, oh, he's
makin' some fancy moves!

16:34.127 --> 16:34.960
All right.

16:36.370 --> 16:37.203
Two,

16:38.938 --> 16:39.771
one.

16:43.348 --> 16:45.931
Yes, and the crowd goes wild!

16:47.648 --> 16:48.481
Yes!

16:50.160 --> 16:51.780
So Kobe, how do you feel

16:54.160 --> 16:55.610
about talkin' to a counselor?

16:57.390 --> 16:58.373
It's whatever.

17:03.510 --> 17:05.203
So are we gonna talk about this?

17:06.619 --> 17:08.709
Well, I was looking forward

17:08.710 --> 17:10.229
to having a long conversation...

17:10.230 --> 17:11.380
Being serious, buddy.

17:17.780 --> 17:20.180
You know, you don't have
to tell her everything.

17:24.637 --> 17:28.128
You just want to be
careful, you know, for me,

17:28.130 --> 17:30.659
for you, for us.

17:30.660 --> 17:31.493
I know.

17:35.010 --> 17:35.843
Cool.

17:41.620 --> 17:42.731
Oh, I forgot something.

17:42.732 --> 17:43.565
What?

17:43.566 --> 17:45.026
This.
No!

17:45.027 --> 17:46.543
Put me down!

17:46.544 --> 17:48.211
No, no, put me down!

17:49.993 --> 17:50.842
He's a winner!

17:50.842 --> 17:51.675
No!

17:51.676 --> 17:53.008
He's a winner!

18:27.543 --> 18:29.143
Mila, Mila Thompson.

18:31.726 --> 18:33.139
Wally?

18:33.140 --> 18:34.483
What are you doing here?

18:35.330 --> 18:36.543
I transferred.

18:38.130 --> 18:39.280
Wally, I can't breathe.

18:40.150 --> 18:41.529
You moved back without calling me?

18:41.530 --> 18:44.629
I know, we just moved back last month.

18:44.630 --> 18:47.109
You look as good as the
day we graduated high school!

18:47.110 --> 18:49.873
Well, on that day, I
was six months pregnant.

18:52.100 --> 18:52.933
Wally,

18:54.370 --> 18:55.260
how are you?

18:55.261 --> 18:58.403
Oh, you know, I'm good, fine, perfect.

19:00.210 --> 19:03.519
Unemployed, per usual, and
always looking for a story.

19:03.520 --> 19:05.249
You know, I sent cover
letters and articles,

19:05.250 --> 19:07.069
but people must use it to wipe their ass

19:07.070 --> 19:09.169
'cause I don't get so much as a you suck.

19:09.170 --> 19:10.699
On top of which, Mom left,

19:10.700 --> 19:13.109
so now I'm raising my sister with Dad.

19:13.110 --> 19:13.943
Sorry.

19:13.944 --> 19:15.549
Oh, it's fine.

19:15.550 --> 19:16.893
Life is what it is.

19:19.160 --> 19:20.609
What are you doing here?

19:20.610 --> 19:23.603
Oh, I'm just visiting my sister, Maddie.

19:24.910 --> 19:26.336
Why?

19:26.337 --> 19:27.303
Oh, you know, the school
said Charley Thompson,

19:27.304 --> 19:29.489
and I just didn't put it together.

19:29.490 --> 19:31.723
Charley, my Charley?

19:32.730 --> 19:35.669
Yes, he was involved in
an altercation with Maddie,

19:35.670 --> 19:37.589
some schoolyard tantrum, you pick on me,

19:37.590 --> 19:39.239
I pick on you thing.

19:39.240 --> 19:40.709
I'm sorry, I had no idea.

19:40.710 --> 19:43.293
Doctor said she'll be okay,
she'll be out in no time.

19:44.590 --> 19:47.040
How have you been here a
month and not called me?

19:50.840 --> 19:52.293
My mom got really sick.

19:55.720 --> 19:57.123
And actually, she died.

19:59.660 --> 20:00.493
Geez.

20:02.090 --> 20:02.923
I'm sorry.

20:04.560 --> 20:05.393
It's fine.

20:07.300 --> 20:09.959
I haven't really been
talking to anyone about it.

20:09.960 --> 20:12.289
I don't know what to say, really.

20:12.290 --> 20:16.039
We moved back so Logan could fix her house

20:16.040 --> 20:17.283
before we sold it.

20:18.450 --> 20:20.273
He's still doing construction.

20:21.350 --> 20:22.183
Cool.

20:27.490 --> 20:28.323
It's hell.

20:30.830 --> 20:32.830
Wally, I wish I was back in high school.

20:41.080 --> 20:41.913
You're sweet.

20:44.090 --> 20:46.099
Logan, didn't tell me anything happened

20:46.100 --> 20:48.009
with Charley at school.

20:48.010 --> 20:49.219
Well, maybe he didn't know.

20:49.220 --> 20:50.403
Yeah, likely story.

20:51.550 --> 20:53.137
They cover for each other.

21:08.748 --> 21:12.529
Thank you, Lenie, but not tonight.

21:29.810 --> 21:31.269
Really?

22:11.624 --> 22:14.823
No, no, no, stop, stop, stop!

22:16.038 --> 22:18.146
Hey, honey, honey, it's okay.

22:18.147 --> 22:22.382
Baby boy, hey, it's okay,

22:22.383 --> 22:23.800
just a bad dream.

22:29.089 --> 22:30.756
Go brush your teeth.

22:32.668 --> 22:36.251
I don't want to brush my teeth.

22:38.115 --> 22:39.024
Goodnight!

22:39.025 --> 22:40.554
Goodnight.

22:59.221 --> 23:01.682
I said I'm doing it.

23:01.683 --> 23:02.516
What?

23:03.987 --> 23:05.237
What are you...

23:10.158 --> 23:11.408
Love you, babe.

23:43.500 --> 23:45.793
Shave if you're gonna do that.

23:48.648 --> 23:49.859
Were you planning on telling me

23:49.860 --> 23:52.010
about what happened
with Charley at school?

23:55.730 --> 23:58.083
I was waiting until you were relaxed,

23:59.790 --> 24:02.330
which is what I'm in here trying to do.

24:06.480 --> 24:10.103
Oh, Mrs. Thompson, you
have, quite possibly,

24:11.360 --> 24:12.410
the very best

24:15.740 --> 24:18.600
knees of anyone

24:19.870 --> 24:20.822
I've ever seen.

24:20.822 --> 24:21.655
Logan,

24:23.321 --> 24:25.733
you haven't put me in the
mood to come home to this.

24:27.000 --> 24:29.823
You're Charley's dad, it's a school night.

24:31.010 --> 24:33.317
What kind of rules are
you settin' for our son?

24:34.710 --> 24:36.878
Yeah, I'm not perfect,

24:36.879 --> 24:38.879
established that when I flunked algebra.

24:40.910 --> 24:45.049
And just to be exact,
it's been three weeks,

24:45.050 --> 24:47.363
four days, five hours.

24:48.774 --> 24:50.149
What?

24:50.150 --> 24:51.073
Since what?

24:53.253 --> 24:55.829
Since the sausage went in the biscuit.

24:55.830 --> 24:58.426
Charley was playing
with your phone again.

24:58.427 --> 24:59.260
Huh?

24:59.261 --> 25:02.119
I said Charley was playing
games on your phone again,

25:02.120 --> 25:03.803
and now, your phone is cracked.

25:07.350 --> 25:08.183
Oh.

25:11.839 --> 25:13.799
Since the ham went in the sandwich.

25:13.800 --> 25:17.149
Dammit, Logan, have you
fixed anything in this house?

25:17.150 --> 25:19.199
Yeah, you know what, I've
been painting the walls

25:19.200 --> 25:20.269
in every room.

25:20.270 --> 25:24.189
But if you want, why don't you
give me a prioritized list,

25:24.190 --> 25:26.909
you can sign off on it at
the end of every night.

25:26.910 --> 25:28.058
How does that sound?

25:49.450 --> 25:51.769
I wish you and me got married,

25:51.770 --> 25:55.679
'cause you and I know how to
have a civilized conversation

25:55.680 --> 25:59.339
without it ending in someone
saying something retarded.

25:59.340 --> 26:01.543
Well, you know, I'm still available.

26:03.040 --> 26:05.590
Get off the phone, you're
keeping your sister up.

26:06.955 --> 26:09.205
Slamming my door's helping!

26:09.206 --> 26:12.752
I have to move out,
I'm too old for this shit!

26:12.753 --> 26:15.959
I know, you're so pathetic.

26:15.960 --> 26:18.000
You should move in with us, but

26:20.270 --> 26:22.920
I actually don't think living
here can be any better.

26:24.280 --> 26:27.123
The school called about
Charley's behavior again today.

26:30.970 --> 26:32.989
Charley knows we've been fighting.

26:32.990 --> 26:34.563
I'm sorry, that sucks.

26:38.820 --> 26:41.893
Wally, I miss our moms.

26:46.295 --> 26:47.793
It's awful living here.

26:49.830 --> 26:51.053
Death is so shitty.

26:51.920 --> 26:54.503
I hear ya, death is lame.

27:29.108 --> 27:30.941
I got you some food.

27:36.450 --> 27:37.300
You've gotta eat.

27:38.360 --> 27:41.590
Remember, you like the
food from this place, Ma.

29:22.127 --> 29:24.813
You know, Emai, I lost him too.

29:26.090 --> 29:26.923
You know that?

29:29.910 --> 29:33.173
He was my best friend, my best friend.

29:39.934 --> 29:42.023
Now I feel like I'm losing you.

30:02.960 --> 30:06.253
Okay, okay, okay, listen, Emai,

30:08.409 --> 30:10.453
I made a big decision, okay?

30:12.490 --> 30:14.193
I'm going to let you set me up.

30:21.695 --> 30:24.659
But only on one condition.

30:24.660 --> 30:26.879
You have to take these black clothes off.

30:26.880 --> 30:28.843
No!
Oh, yes, yes, yes, yes, yes!

30:28.844 --> 30:29.969
No, no, no, no, no, no, no!

30:29.970 --> 30:32.262
It doesn't mean you're losing him.

30:32.263 --> 30:33.613
These are just clothes, Ma!

30:35.863 --> 30:36.696
Come on.

30:37.690 --> 30:40.629
Believe me, Abell and
Pa would be more upset

30:40.630 --> 30:42.646
to see you wearing these
clothes than out of them.

30:42.647 --> 30:44.360
You have to do it for them.

30:46.010 --> 30:46.843
Okay?

30:55.096 --> 30:55.929
Fine.

30:58.460 --> 31:00.296
But this is our deal.

31:00.297 --> 31:01.714
Okay, our deal.

31:10.800 --> 31:12.449
Beyonce's tits.

31:12.450 --> 31:14.879
Excuse you, Charley, we're
not talking about Beyonce here,

31:14.880 --> 31:16.519
so you're gonna have to
think of something else

31:16.520 --> 31:18.143
besides a celebrity, okay?

31:20.710 --> 31:21.809
Your mom.

31:21.810 --> 31:24.037
Charley, you are out of
line, you need to apologize.

31:25.470 --> 31:26.619
Is he gonna be okay?

31:26.620 --> 31:28.409
Ask him yourself.

31:28.410 --> 31:30.049
You're the freakin' therapist!

31:30.050 --> 31:30.883
Charley!

31:45.389 --> 31:46.685
Hey, Lenie!

32:10.840 --> 32:14.898
How can I resist
this whimsical spirit?

33:20.591 --> 33:23.174
Hey, you want a ride?

33:26.375 --> 33:27.979
I guess so because I'm freezing.

33:27.980 --> 33:29.837
My feet are cold.

33:36.786 --> 33:39.703
Thank you.

33:41.962 --> 33:43.462
So, how's Charley?

33:46.980 --> 33:48.313
Unpredictable.

33:49.870 --> 33:51.020
No more notes, right?

33:51.980 --> 33:54.253
Yeah, so far, so good.

33:56.285 --> 33:57.879
Chocolate?

33:57.880 --> 33:58.713
I'm all right.

33:58.713 --> 33:59.546
You look really good.

34:00.580 --> 34:02.230
Women don't wear dresses anymore.

34:03.422 --> 34:06.063
I guess a dress makes you
feel like a lady, right?

34:08.949 --> 34:10.186
Totally.

34:13.532 --> 34:15.989
What if I dared you to wear jeans?

34:15.989 --> 34:18.659
Course I do, it's all I
used to do when I was a kid.

34:18.659 --> 34:20.168
I was a tomboy, you know?

34:20.170 --> 34:21.003
Really?
Yeah.

34:21.004 --> 34:23.609
I would have never ever guessed that.

34:23.610 --> 34:24.719
Yeah, I was.

34:24.719 --> 34:26.714
Like, tomboy like you
used to play sports?

34:26.715 --> 34:28.039
Of course.

34:28.040 --> 34:30.668
I was in every team you
can think of at school.

34:30.670 --> 34:32.223
You look so uncoordinated.

34:32.224 --> 34:33.222
Oh, my God!

34:40.260 --> 34:41.092
Turn left here.

34:42.540 --> 34:44.129
Why'd you point right, though?

34:44.130 --> 34:47.487
Oh, sorry, I'm dyslexic, you know?

34:47.489 --> 34:49.067
Oh, that makes sense.

34:53.306 --> 34:55.268
You know, I have the same
problem with my mom's ring

34:55.270 --> 34:57.270
that she gave me, it's a little too big.

34:58.730 --> 35:00.499
Yeah, I got mine when I was 17.

35:00.500 --> 35:04.259
Fingers were all ballooned up
from taking too many steroids.

35:04.260 --> 35:06.119
Wow, that sounds unhealthy to me.

35:06.120 --> 35:08.179
The marriage or the steroids?

35:08.180 --> 35:09.380
Why so young?

35:11.050 --> 35:13.708
You remember that
11-year-old in your office?

35:13.709 --> 35:16.379
He pretty much sealed the deal.

35:16.380 --> 35:19.193
I don't know, it's hard, but it's good.

35:20.910 --> 35:23.032
It's right over here.

35:23.033 --> 35:24.729
Really, you live right here?

